reviews.review:
I've been playing Dead By Daylight for years on my PS4 and I have always loved it. It's my most consistent online game. The characters are a-plenty and the addition of licensed characters is a really cool and big plus. There's not really any other game where you can have characters from Resident Evil, Halloween, Stranger Things, Saw, and Left for Dead all in a match together- and that's not counting the other iconic franchises they under their belt I'm too lazy to add to the list. Their original characters are also very interesting and the lore behind the game is extensive and neat for those who like that sort of thing. You can just as easily play without reading any of it, too. The inability to fight back leads to some truly fun and interesting mind-games and strategies to keep from dying or killing survivors. I love horror and I love the concept and execution of this game. It has its issues, like any game, but honestly in the grand scheme of things I don't mind when I enjoy the game this much. 

My biggest gripe is the lack of cross-progression. I was devotion 3 in my PS4 account with 4 prestige 3 characters and a LOT of things unlocked and purchased (after years of gameplay), and now that I'm on pc I lose all of that and have to start back at square one. It stings and I miss my characters and their skins and perks ;^;

But yeah! Love this game regardless and at least my best pal is also starting over so I don't have to do it alone :)
